                            <comment id="82635" author="jamesanunez" created="Mon, 28 Apr 2014 16:59:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch 10104 was abandoned because &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/10091&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/10091&lt;/a&gt; incorporates all of these changes. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="82511" author="jamesanunez" created="Fri, 25 Apr 2014 17:43:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In patch 9910, a comment requested that the lfsck_start --windows option be changed to --window. That change is in the patch at &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/10104&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/10104&lt;/a&gt; . &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Only the lfsck_start option was changed. Internal use of &quot;windows&quot; was not changed for routine names, variables or constants.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="81174" author="jamesanunez" created="Tue, 8 Apr 2014 14:42:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The updated lctl man page patch at &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/9910&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/9910&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="81162" author="adilger" created="Tue, 8 Apr 2014 11:26:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That patch is for the Lustre manual. The lustre/doc/lctl.8 man page should also be updated to describe these new options. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
